# Files to Update When Adding New Meeple States, Actions, or Inventory Items

## When Adding a New Meeple State

1. **`src/types.ts`**
   - Add the new state name to the `MeepleStateNames` enum
   - Create a new state type (e.g., `MeepleStateNewState`)
   - Add the new state type to the `MeepleState` union type

2. **`src/Game/Meeple.ts`**
   - Add a case in the `dispatch()` method's switch statement to handle the new state

3. **`src/components/StateType.tsx`**
   - Add a case in the `getStateColor()` switch statement to assign a color badge for the new state

4. **`src/components/HistoryItem.tsx`**
   - Add a case in the switch statement to render the new state in the history display

5. **`src/utils/iconMap.ts`**
   - Add an icon mapping for the new state in the `IconMap` object

## When Adding a New Meeple Action

1. **`src/types.ts`**
   - Create a new action type (e.g., `MeepleActionNewAction`)
   - Add the new action type to the `MeepleAction` union type

2. **`src/Game/Meeple.ts`**
   - Add a case in the `dispatch()` method's switch statement to handle the new action
   - Implement the action logic (if needed)

3. **`src/utils/iconMap.ts`**
   - Add an icon mapping for the new action in the `IconMap` object

4. **`src/Game/conditions.ts`** (if applicable)
   - Update condition actions to use the new action type if needed

## When Adding a New Meeple Inventory Item

1. **`src/types.ts`**
   - Add the new item to the `MeepleInventoryItem` enum

2. **`src/consts.ts`**
   - Add the new item to `DEFAULT_INVENTORY` with a default value (usually 0)
   - Add to `TRANSMUTATION_RATIOS` if the item can be transmuted from/to
   - Add to `SELL_PRICES` if the item can be sold
   - Add to `BUY_PRICES` if the item can be bought

3. **`src/utils/iconMap.ts`**
   - Add an icon mapping for the new inventory item in the `IconMap` object

4. **`src/components/ProductsChart.tsx`** (if applicable)
   - Add aggregation logic to track the new inventory item in charts

5. **`src/components/Stats.tsx`** (if applicable)
   - Add stats tracking for the new inventory item (counts, filtering, etc.)

6. **`src/Game/conditions.ts`** (if applicable)
   - Update conditions that reference inventory items to use the new item if needed
